cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual simultaneous localization and mapping (vSLAM) system which is a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper integrates the motion removal approach with the ORB-SLAM2 system which is a popular visual SLAM system used in robotics. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper proposes a weakly-supervised semantic segmentation method that leverages the power of deep semantic segmentation CNNs. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel approach to solve the problem of movable objects in vSLAM systems. 
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper presents experimental results on two popular computer vision datasets.
